  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Sitting Alone
  author: Kwon Dam
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I linger in dreams unfinished at dawn,
    Drawing the silk quilt close around me again.
    Spring warms the heavens and earth anew,
    While books and scrolls deepen my small study.
    Though I hide away on Southern Mountain,
    My loyal heart still faces the Northern Palace.
    With age, fewer companions seek me out—
    Only quiet birds draw near the bamboo grove.
  footnotes:
    - Southern Mountain (南山) and Northern Palace (北闕) are classical references suggesting retreat from court life while maintaining allegiance to the throne
    - The contrast between withdrawal and continued loyalty reflects the tension common in Korean literati of the Joseon period between private cultivation and public duty
